               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602010177"></xptr>
               <p>About half-past four o'clock in the afternoon, on the 30th of January, I was going down Coventry-street—I felt a tug at my pocket—I turned and seized the prisoner with my left, hand, with my other hand I took this handkerchief, which he was concealing in his bosom—it is mine—he was very peaceable, and burst out crying—he did not deny the charge.</p>
